The paper deals with the design and analysis of a communication system, specifically a spatial-division multiple-access (SDMA) system, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the system's performance and optimization, which falls under the category of control and systems engineering (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of machine learning techniques for channel estimation, which could be classified under multimedia (cs.MM) or machine learning (cs.LG).
